wikipedia_page.main: Dennis O'Neill is a World Cup winning former professional rugby league footballer who played in the 1960s and 1970s. He played at representative level for Great Britain and Lancashire, and at club level for Widnes and Oldham (Heritage № 852), as a stand-off, i.e. number 6.
